tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows mild hypoglycemia, elevated creatinine suggesting impaired renal function, mildly elevated ALT indicating possible liver involvement, low total bilirubin, and low HDL cholesterol. Other parameters are within normal limits. Recommend clinical correlation for renal and hepatic function, and monitoring of glucose and lipid profile.
